PRIVACY POLICY
updated April 30, 2021
Welcome to CamToPlan’s privacy policy. We are a company called Tasmanic Editions S.A.S. We are registered in France with number 794114934. Our address is 91 Rue du Faubourg Saint-Honoré, 75008 Paris, FRANCE.
This policy describes how we (referred in this policy as ‘Tasmanic’ or ‘we’, us’ and ‘our’) collect, use, process and share information that Tasmanic collects about you when you use the app 'CamToPlan' on your iOS device, starting version 3.7.
For previous versions of the app, please refer to
this privacy policy
which applies to the former versions of the app before version 3.7
Those policies only apply to this app on iOS devices and NOT to our other products, services or businesses.
If you have any concerns about this privacy policy you should not use this app.
1- Age requirements
THIS SERVICE IS NOT MEANT FOR PEOPLE UNDER 16. We are committed to protecting the privacy needs of children and we encourage parents and guardians to take an active role in their children's online activities and interests. We do not knowingly collect information from children under the age of 16 and we do not target this Service to children under 16. If we receive a valid notice through dpo@tasmanic.com that a minor under age of 16 has provided us with personal information, we will take measures to delete it as soon as possible.
2- Why Do we Collect data ?
Like most of the other app publishers, Tasmanic Editions needs to perform some R&D, analysis and marketing tasks. We explain here the reasons why we and our partners may collect data:
- Internal analytics and reporting,
- Operate our business and app,
- App mechanics or functionality,
- Maintaining and enhancing service, debugging,
- Product development/improvement,
- Internal research,
- Customer service,
- User acquisition,
- Advertising and direct marketing,
- Detecting/protecting against security events, preventing fraud and abuse of our policies,
- Compliance purposes and meeting legal/regulatory requirements.
3- Data that may be collected
App usage
Examples: navigation inside the app, actions in the app such as clicks on buttons, duration of sessions, frequency of use...
This data is generally analyzed through aggregated reports.
Technical Data
Examples: identifiers such as the Apple's identifier for vendors (the ‘IDFV’), IP address, device country or language, device screen size, operating system and version...
These technologies may allow us to recognize the users devices, provide interest-based advertising and allow us to understand how the users interact with our app.
Messages
If you contact us, for instance by email or on our social media channels, we may keep a record of that correspondence.
4- Data we don't collect and don't share
All the plans, measures, documents titles and folders that you create within the app are only stored on your device. We don't collect information about them.
5- Our Partners
We currently work with carefully selected and trustful partners.
Data Processors:
- Gandi
It's our Web hosting service provider.
learn more
- Apple
We measure our campaigns performances through the Apple SKAdnetwork framework in order to protect our users privacy.
learn more
Data Controllers:
- Apple App Store
All apps downloads, in-app purchases and subscriptions performed from the app are managed by Apple which manages the App Store. Their Privacy Policy can be viewed
here
6- Opt-out
The collection of personal data in the app depends on your consent through a 'pop-up' shown at the first launch of the app.
You can give or withdraw your consent at anytime in the app itself : in the menu on the main page, open the 'privacy settings'.
You can select 'On' to allow the collection of personal data or 'Off' to disallow the collection of personal data.
Click 'OK' to submit your new settings.
Then force the app to close  (
more info
)
Then restart the app.
7- Payments
All payments for products bought within the app, such as in-app purchases or subscriptions, are managed and processed by Apple which manages the Appstore.
8- GDPR - Additional rights in the EEA or Switzerland
- Request access to and receive information about the Personal Information we maintain about you, to update and correct inaccuracies in your Personal Information, restrict or to object to the processing of your Personal Information, have the information anonymized or deleted, as appropriate, or exercise your right to data portability to easily transfer your Personal Information to another company. In addition, you may also have the right to lodge a complaint with the CNIL which is the supervisory authority In France.
- Withdraw any consent you previously provided to us regarding the processing of your Personal Information, at any time and free of charge. We will apply your preferences going forward and this will not affect the lawfulness of the processing before your consent withdrawal.
Those rights may be limited in some circumstances by local law requirements. You may exercise these rights by using the 'How to Contact Us' section below.
9- CCPA Consumer Rights (Additional California Privacy Rights)
This section provides additional details for California consumers about the rights afforded to them under the California Consumer Privacy Act or 'CCPA'.
California Children Under 16
THIS SERVICE IS NOT MEANT FOR CALIFORNIA-LOCATED PEOPLE UNDER 16.
Your Rights Regarding Personal Information.
Under the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018 ('the CCPA'), California consumers have the right to request access to the specific pieces of personal information we have collected about them in the last 12 months. You may also request additional details about our information practices, including the categories of personal information we have collected about you, the categories of sources of such collection, the business or commercial purpose for collecting personal information, the categories of third parties with whom we share your personal information, the categories of personal information we have disclosed about you in the preceding 12 months. If you are a California consumer, you also have the right to request deletion of your personal information (subject to certain exceptions), to opt out of sales of personal information and to receive equal service and price and not be discriminated against even if you exercise any of their other CCPA rights.
You can only make a personal information request twice in a 12-month period, we will respond within 45 days of receiving a personal information request.
To exercise any of the above rights, please contact us using the following information and submit the required verifying information, as further described below: please email dpo@tasmanic.com or contact us using this address: Tasmanic Editions, 91 rue du Faubourg Saint Honoré, 75008 Paris, France
Verification Process and Required Information :
Note that we may need to request additional information from you to verify your identity or understand the scope of your request, although you will not be required to create an account with us to submit a request or have it fulfilled. In the event you designate an authorized agent to make a CCPA request on your behalf, we will require verification of identity and authorization.
