PRIVACY POLICY
updated June 25, 2020
Welcome to CamToPlan’s privacy policy! We are a company called Tasmanic Editions S.A.S. We are registered in France with number 794114934. Our address is 91 Rue du Faubourg Saint-Honoré, 75008 Paris, FRANCE.
This policy describes how we (referred in this policy as ‘Tasmanic’ or ‘we’, us’ and ‘our’) collect, use, process and share information that Tasmanic collects about you when you use the apps 'CamToPlan' or 'CamToPlan PRO'.
If you have any concerns about this privacy policy you should not use our apps or other Services.
1- Age requirements
THIS SERVICE IS NOT MEANT FOR PEOPLE UNDER 16. We are committed to protecting the privacy needs of children and we encourage parents and guardians to take an active role in their children's online activities and interests. We do not knowingly collect information from children under the age of 16 and we do not target this Service to children under 16. If we receive a valid notice through dpo@tasmanic.com that a minor under age of 16 has provided us with personal information, we will take measures to delete it as soon as possible.
2- Why Do we Collect data ?
Like most of the other app publishers, Tasmanic Editions needs to perform some R&D, analysis and marketing tasks. We explain here the reasons why we and our partners may collect data:
- Internal analytics and reporting,
- Operate our business and app,
- App mechanics or functionality,
- Maintaining and enhancing service, debugging,
- Detecting/Protecting against security event,
- Product development/improvement,
- Internal research,
- Customer service,
- User acquisition,
- Advertising and direct marketing,
- Detecting/protecting against security events, preventing fraud and abuse of our policies,
- Compliance purposes and meeting legal/regulatory requirements.
3- Data that may be collected
App usage
Examples: navigation inside the app, actions in the app such as clicks on buttons, duration of sessions, frequency of use...
This data is generally analyzed through aggregated reports.
Technical Data
Examples: ad identifiers, IP address, device country or language, device screen size, operating system and version...
ad identifiers are non-permanent identifiers such as the Android advertising ID and/or Apple's ID for advertising (the ‘IDFA’), which are uniquely associated with your device.
These technologies may allow us and our partners to recognize the users devices, provide interest-based advertising and allow us to understand how the users interact with our app.
Messages
If you contact us, for instance by email, we may keep a record of that correspondence.
Your interactions with us on our social media channels.
4- Data we don't collect and don't share
All the plans, measures, documents titles and folders that you create within the app are only stored on your device. We don't collect information about them and we ensure our partners can't access them.
Please take appropriate measures to backup your device frequently because there's no way for us to help you retrieve this data in case a problem occurs (ex: device broken ...)
5- Our Partners
